Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.64,0:40:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,later misunderstandings of the teacher\Nof the Buddha. There's no lesser and
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.28,0:40:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,greater. Those are already judgmental\Nand
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.68,0:40:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and the conceptualization. There's no\Nlesser and greater.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.76,0:40:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Is there any real enlightenment if it's\Nnot involved with the suffering that's
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.20,0:41:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,in our in the world that we live in?\N>> The suffering of the world you live in
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.07,0:41:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is your own perception. From another\Nperception, there isn't any suffering in
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.48,0:41:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the world.\NIf I tell you to stop suffering, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.00,0:41:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,stop suffering in an instant. I've done\Nit when I fractured my ankle. I just got
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.59,0:41:18.31,Default,,0,0,0,,through telling you there's no\Nsuffering. You let go resisting,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.31,0:41:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering disappears.\NWell, just in our century, there's a 100
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.96,0:41:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,million people who have been slaughtered\Nby other
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.44,0:41:29.83,Default,,0,0,0,,>> That's right. Sounds awful, don't it?\N>> Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.83,0:41:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sounds awful.\N>> How do you know that it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.59,0:41:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,>> You don't.\NWe presume that that is so. Yeah. We
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.31,0:41:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,presume that is so.\N>> In other words, there's that there's no
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.92,0:41:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,value judgment attached to that. No\Nvalue judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.76,0:41:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The viewpoint of\Nthe viewpoint of Shiva,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.00,0:41:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the dance of Shiva. It looks this way,\Nthis way. It looks this way, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.48,0:42:04.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's only a perception and a\Nmoralistic judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.35,0:42:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,From another viewpoint, the death of 10\Nmillion people is nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.20,0:42:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,They've done it a zillion times already.\NSo, what's one more time?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.88,0:42:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called the spiritual skeptic.\NOkay. Thank you. And my last one. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.35,0:42:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Mhm.\N>> Hi. Um, my question is in regards to
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.20,0:42:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,unconditional love and You guys what?\N>> Unconditional love. And you you talk
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.80,0:42:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about\N>> what kind of love?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.00,0:42:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Unconditional love.\N>> Oh, unconditional love. Yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.20,0:42:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Sorry. Um in respect to the naive side\Nto it. Um often I find my mind or um
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.92,0:43:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,gets caught up in\Njudging the love of even idiots or as
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.44,0:43:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you as you would you know. But I get\NI get caught up in okay why can't why is
