Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.72,0:53:17.83,Default,,0,0,0,,you, that's oppression.\NTo be born to born to a famous family
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.83,0:53:22.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and be worth a hundred million when the\Nminute you're born
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.16,0:53:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,carries worries and responsibilities and\Nsleepless nights that you wouldn't even
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.20,0:53:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,dream of.\Nuh responsibility in the ethics and
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.64,0:53:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,what's your responsibility to the world\Nand the temptation to be arrogant,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.44,0:53:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,temptation to be callous,\Ntemptation to abuse power and privilege.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:45.92,0:53:50.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see the karmic responsibility\Ninherent to everyone's
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.24,0:53:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,circumstances. your birth. You look back\Nat your own birth and uh
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.44,0:54:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it's hard to see, but if you\Nlook at it from the viewpoint I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.31,0:54:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioning, you'll notice it was really\Nquite perfect.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.52,0:54:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,As a kid, I didn't think so, that's for\Nsure.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.92,0:54:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. Life in the 30s in the Midwest\Nduring the depression was arduous.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.68,0:54:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Arduous. arduous.\NEvery day was a 12-hour day of one kind
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.76,0:54:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or another.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.48,0:54:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NBut side was the camaraderie of World
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.96,0:54:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,War II. America was completely united,\Nunified, completely at one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.68,0:54:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You couldn't have won without Rosie the\NRibbiter.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.48,0:54:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody played an important part.\NImportant part.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:53.04,0:54:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Kids like myself save scrap metal for\Nthe war effort. You know, there was a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.00,0:55:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous unity to that generation. It\Nwas really fun. You know,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.80,0:55:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you know,\Nmore doctors smoke camels than any other
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.44,0:55:21.24,Default,,0,0,0,,cigarette.\NThey're good for your T-zone.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.20,0:55:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And then on television, there were\Ndancing jello- boxes, you know. And
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.00,0:55:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Sunday, everybody gathered and sat on\Nthe bed and turned on the radio, you
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.48,0:55:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,know, radio Filco,\NAM radio, and you listen to Jack Benny
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.88,0:55:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,and Red Skeleton. And\Nit was an era that the young people
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.07,0:55:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,today uh that never got to experience of\Nthe whole country being united like one
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.16,0:55:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,big family\Nand everybody hitchhiked everywhere. I
Dialogue: 0,0:55:58.88,0:56:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,had to hitchhike every day 10 miles to\Nthe high school which was in town
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.52,0:56:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because I lived out in the country.\NSo, you know, 10 below zero, you get on
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.68,0:56:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this highway, there was one car every\N15, 20 minutes
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.76,0:56:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'd hear a car coming down, you\Nknow, a truck. Whoa. I could hear a
